{
  "texts": [
    "An example of this is the message passing NN [63], where the following invariant is exploited:v s i e i -----→ v r i (80)In a directed graph 28, each edge e i has a sender node v s i and a receiver node v r i.",
    "This enables the formulation of an algorithm operating first on the edges, and subsequently on the nodes, as summarized in Algorithm 1 for a single graph block.",
    "These graph blocks can be stacked similarly to layers in other NN architectures.Algorithm 1 Graph block in a message passing NN.",
    "Nodes v, edges e, and global attributes u are updated with conventional FC-NNs f v, f e, f u.",
    "To incorporate all the relevant information with a variable size as input to these FC-NNs, aggregation operations are performed ρ e→v, ρ e→u, ρ e→v."
  ]
}